<br>
e: Earring of Veracity *new thread*<br>
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------<br>
 Grabbing back to what Tilbok said:<br>
<br>
<br>
Quote:<br>
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------<br>
 Tilbok Furruner reads through the report, hands you a small satchel then starts to explain, 'Finally news from Euzan. I knew that it would take a long time to get planted within Seru, but i still worried about their mission constantly. This report shows that you have earned trust from Euzan, so I in turn will show the same trust. Euzan and Torsten were placed in the city for information. They are deep undercover and risk their life everyday. Every person in that city is ingrained with the [purpose] of either destroying Katta or converting his people.'<br>
<br>
You say, 'what purpose?'<br>
<br>
Tilbok Furrunner says 'The teaching in the city is that Katta feigned his death to blame it on Seru. When in fact Seru actually poisoned Katta. The crusade that Seru leads is false and must be stopped. We must gain access to Seru's [chambers] and destroy him and show the city the truth.<br>
<br>
You say, 'what chambers?'<br>
<br>
Tilbok Furrunner says ' We do not know much about Seru's Chamber, that is what we need you to find out. This will require great effort on your part. We need you to infiltrate Sanctus Seru and bring back reports from each Consillium. I do not know who will have these reports, and I have only heard rumor that they exist. Return to me with the Satchel full, and your Etched Earring.<br>
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
While reading through the posted suggestions, I keep seeing people assuming messengers or couriers who will transport to reports you are looking for to Seru himself, or something.<br>
<br>
I think - based on the above information from Tilbok - that this is actually in the wrong direction. The reports are not transported anywhere or anything, but they rather detail about the security of Seru and his residence. No matter how much they may hate one another, all four Consiliums are working to protect Seru ultimately.<br>
<br>
Each Consilium is specialised in one specific direction. As such, each Consilium will be responsible for the defense and security of his housing in the field in which they are active. Their activities in keeping it tight is covered in those reports.<br>
<br>
Considering their envy, they are most likely trying to keep these reports away from the prying eyes of the other Consiliums. But combined, these reports give one hell of a good idea of the layout and functioning of the security of the house in which Seru can be found.<br>
<br>
You are not required to enter Seru's Chambers just yet - you must gather information on it first. Reconnaisance. Spying. Infiltration.<br>
<br>
I don't know how, where or when, but I personally think the reports are found inside each Consilium.  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/utynkmindrifter.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Tynk Mindrifter</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/7/02 10:21:34 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Reports</span><hr size=1> ok guys<br>
